title: Tigre, Argentina
text:
Only registered TrekEarth members may write critiques. Photographer's Note 
This city is the metropolitan area of Buenos Aires. It is known as the "Venice" of Buenos Aires. At this point the grand rivers that run through South America, north to south, flow into the sea. Some of them are the Paran√° River and the Uruguay River, but we have dozens of other smaller and secondary rivers. In this city these rivers mingle and open in what we call "delta", forming small channels. In this city the dozens of houses located in the lower regions of the delta where the only way to get there is boat. Tigre, Buenos Aires, Argentina.
